fields.description: The President serves as the Commander-in-Chief of the Kenya Defence Forces and chairs the National Security Council.
fields.title: Commander-in-Chief of the Defence Forces

fields.description: The President is the Head of State and Government and the symbol of national unity.
fields.title: Head of State and Government

fields.description: The President must respect, uphold, and safeguard the Constitution of Kenya 2010.
fields.title: Uphold and Safeguard the Constitution

fields.description: The President must promote and enhance the unity of the nation and respect the diversity of the people.
fields.title: Promote Unity of the Nation

fields.description: The President ensures the protection of human rights and fundamental freedoms as provided in the Constitution.
fields.title: Protect Human Rights and Freedoms

fields.description: The President ensures the sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity of Kenya is safeguarded.
fields.title: Protect Sovereignty of the Republic

fields.description: The President addresses Parliament at the opening of each new session and submits annual reports on the state of the nation.
fields.title: Address Parliament

fields.description: The President nominates, appoints, or dismisses State and public officers as provided by the Constitution.
fields.title: Appoint Public Officers

fields.description: The President conducts and coordinates Kenya’s foreign relations and receives foreign diplomatic representatives.
fields.title: Conduct Foreign Policy

fields.description: The President, with approval of Parliament, may declare war or a state of emergency.
fields.title: Declare War or Emergency

fields.description: The President confers honours in the name of the people and the Republic.
fields.title: Confer Honours

fields.description: Supports the President in executing government functions and national leadership.
fields.title: Assist the President

fields.description: Assumes presidential duties when the President is absent, incapacitated, or otherwise unable to serve.
fields.title: Act as President

fields.description: Oversees performance of ministries as directed by the President.
fields.title: Cabinet Oversight

fields.description: Coordinates government policies across ministries and departments.
fields.title: Policy Coordination

fields.description: Represents the government in national and international functions when delegated by the President.
fields.title: Public Representation

fields.description: The Governor is the chief executive of the county, responsible for implementing county laws and policies.
fields.title: Chief Executive of the County

fields.description: Chairs the County Executive Committee, appoints members (with assembly approval), and provides leadership in county administration.
fields.title: Head of County Executive Committee

fields.description: Ensures implementation of national and county legislation as provided under the Constitution.
fields.title: County Legislation Implementation

fields.description: Oversees the management and use of county resources for the benefit of residents.
fields.title: Management of County Resources

fields.description: Promotes democracy, good governance, unity, and peace within the county.
fields.title: Promotion of Governance

fields.description: Represents the county in national and international functions as required.
fields.title: Representation of the County

fields.description: Provides regular reports to the county assembly on matters of county governance.
fields.title: Accountability

fields.description: The Deputy Governor is the principal assistant of the Governor in executing county functions and may represent the Governor when delegated.
fields.title: Principal Assistant to the Governor

fields.description: If the Governor dies, resigns, is impeached, or is otherwise permanently incapacitated, the Deputy Governor assumes the office of Governor for the remainder of the term.
fields.title: Assumption of Office of Governor

fields.description: When the Governor is temporarily absent, incapacitated, or otherwise unable to act, the Deputy Governor serves as the Acting Governor.
fields.title: Acting Governor

fields.description: Supports the Governor in coordinating and supervising county executive functions, ensuring smooth running of county government.
fields.title: Collaboration with County Executive

fields.description: Senators represent and protect the interests of the counties and their governments in the national arena.
fields.title: Representation of Counties

fields.description: Senators participate in the passing of laws, especially those affecting counties.
fields.title: Participation in Law-making

fields.description: Senators determine how national revenue is shared among the 47 counties.
fields.title: Allocation of National Revenue

fields.description: Senators oversee how county governments utilize national revenue allocated to them.
fields.title: Oversight of Revenue Allocation

fields.description: Senators determine the outcome of impeachment proceedings against Governors.
fields.title: Impeachment Role

fields.description: MPs represent the people of their constituencies in the National Assembly, ensuring that their interests are considered in national debates and decisions.
fields.title: Representation

fields.description: MPs participate in law-making by debating, amending, and passing Bills that affect the country.
fields.title: Legislation

fields.description: MPs oversee the actions of the Executive by scrutinizing policies, budgets, and government operations to ensure accountability and transparency.
fields.title: Oversight

fields.description: MPs play a key role in discussing, amending, and approving the national budget and allocation of public resources.
fields.title: Budget Approval

fields.description: MPs manage the Constituency Development Fund (CDF) and initiate projects that directly benefit their constituents.
fields.title: Constituency Development

fields.description: Represent the residents of their electoral ward in the county assembly.
fields.title: Representation of the Ward

fields.description: Participate in making laws at the county level, particularly those that affect the county and ward residents.
fields.title: Legislation

fields.description: Provide oversight over the County Executive Committee and ensure county resources are used responsibly.
fields.title: Oversight

fields.description: Approve budgets and development plans of the county government, ensuring that local priorities are addressed.
fields.title: Budget Approval

fields.description: Push for development initiatives and allocation of county resources in their respective wards.
fields.title: Development Representation

fields.description: Remain accountable to the electorate by holding regular consultative meetings and maintaining transparency.
fields.title: Accountability to the People

fields.description: Articulate and champion issues affecting women, children, and other vulnerable groups at the National Assembly level.
fields.title: Representation of Women Interests

fields.description: Participate in law-making processes by debating and voting on bills and motions in the National Assembly.
fields.title: Legislative Role

fields.description: Monitor and oversee the use of public resources by the national government, particularly on matters affecting women and marginalized groups.
fields.title: Oversight

fields.description: Promote gender equality and inclusion in political, economic, and social development within counties and nationally.
fields.title: Promoting Gender Equality

fields.description: Ensure representation of marginalized and special interest groups as mandated by the Constitution.
fields.title: Special Interest Representation

fields.description: Engage with county residents to bring their views, petitions, and concerns to the National Assembly.
fields.title: Constituency Engagement
